[SN]TITLE[SN]
Kids' lives and pocket money hit by Greek money problems

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Greece is struggling with big money problems and it's affecting the lives of people living there, including children.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
9 July 2015 Last updated at 08:03 BST
Ricky's been to Greece's capital city Athens to meet children who are off from school for the summer to see how things have changed for them.
From getting less pocket money and shops closing in their local area, they've been telling Ricky what it's been like...
Guide: Why is Greece in so much trouble?
